cs.MA, cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.AR, cs.DC

The paper discusses a framework for mobile immersive computing, which involves multiple applications or users sharing computation-intensive tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Graphics (cs.GR), Augmented Reality (cs.AR), or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). However, since the focus is on mobile devices and edge computing, cs.MA and cs.DC are less likely. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.HC, cs.GR, and cs.AR, in that order.
